  "texts": [
    "As soon as the rotation gates are finished, the ancilla qubits can be rapidly deallocated, allowing the protocol to achieve O(N) spacetime allocation.",
    "The protocol for LOADF is depicted in Fig. 19, with the corresponding pseudocode written in Algorithm 8.m B B D 0: |k⟩ |k⟩B 0: |0 B ⟩ LOADF {θ (k) } s,p R y (f s,p θ (k) s,p) |0⟩ F 0: s,p |f s,p ⟩ s,p |f s,p ⟩ = D: |k⟩ ⊗ |0 O(N) ⟩ Setup Setup † |k⟩ ⊗ |0 O(N) ⟩ B: |0 B ⟩ ⊗ |φ O(N) ⟩ CCRy s,p R y (f s,p θ (k) s,p) |0⟩ ⊗ |φ O(N) ⟩ A: |0 O(N) ⟩ |0 O(N) ⟩ F: s,p |f s,p ⟩ ⊗ |0 O(N) ⟩ s,p |f s,p ⟩ ⊗ |0 O(N) ⟩ m m m m M -m-1 Bm Bm Bm B(M -m-1) B B B (M -1) B M -1 M -1 M -1 M ( B-1) B B B (M-1) B D0: |k⟩ COPY ⊗m B+1 Copy Copy † COPY †⊗m B+1 |k⟩ D1 D2 Copy ⊗ B Copy †⊗ B D3 B0: |0 B ⟩ Swap ⊗ B s,p M -1 j=0 Ry(θ (j) s,p) Swap †⊗ B s,p Ry(fs,pθ (k) s,p) |0⟩ B1 A0: |0⟩ X Swap COPY ⊗M B COPY †⊗M B Swap † X |0⟩ A1 A2 F0: s,p |fs,p⟩ COPY ⊗ B M COPY †⊗ B M s,p |fs,p⟩ F1 s,p, with k = 0,..., M -1, s = 0,..., n -m -1, and p = 0,..., 2 s -1.",
    "For each CCRy gate, one qubit from the final two registers (corresponding to the choice of (s, p)) and one qubit from the three registers above the final two registers (corresponding to the choice of k) acts as a control.",
    "Copying layers before the CCRy sequence is necessary such that these can all be performed in parallel.",
    "After the CCRy sequence, we perform B CopySwap † operations in parallel in order to load the N -M angles into the buffer ancilla of sizeB."
